Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.51,0:00:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, I'm Dr. David R. Hawkins. I'm a physician, psychiatrist, psychoanalyst, nutritionist.\NI've been doing research in the nature of consciousness itself and levels of awareness that the world calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.90,0:00:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of this, plus my 35 years of clinical experience, as well as my own personal experience,\Nwe've derived knowledge that can be extremely useful in alleviating human suffering in all its forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.28,0:00:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,many of which I've lived through in my own personal life,\Nand I've been forced to find answers that are outside the field of traditional medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.88,0:00:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For today, we need to know a little bit more about the nature of consciousness itself.\NWe need to talk about body, mind, spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Holistic Health has used this, body, mind, and spirit.\NIs it just a catchphrase? Is it just a slogan?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.97,0:01:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it really mean, body, mind, and spirit?\NWhat is spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.63,0:01:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, is that a metaphysical abstraction?\NIs that a religious dictum?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.83,0:01:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a fantasy of people who are not too well connected with the real world?\NJust exactly what is this relationship?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.70,0:01:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it will help us and speed up our work with a greater understanding.\NTo begin with, then, we want to describe how human experience comes about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.20,0:01:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of look within ourself to see where this fantasy,\Nthis phenomena, actually occurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.55,0:01:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to look at this relationship now between body, mind, and spirit\Nfrom the viewpoint of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.90,0:01:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll say some things that sound somewhat startling,\Nsuch as, to begin with, the fact that the body cannot experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.29,0:02:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's a startling thought because all of us tend to think of ourselves as being the body.\NWe tend to think, I am the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.29,0:02:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll quickly see, as we go along, that the body cannot experience itself.\NAnd if we look at it, that this is not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.38,0:02:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The body itself is unable to experience itself.\NFor instance, my arm cannot experience its own armness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.38,0:02:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My left arm cannot experience my left armness.\NWhat is actually going on are sensations coming from the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.50,0:02:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're not experiencing the body anyway.\NWe're experiencing the sensations of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.79,0:02:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And these sensations of the body\Ncuriously enough cannot experience themselves either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.79,0:02:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The sensations coming from the arm have to be experienced somewhere.\NAnd where are they being experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.79,0:03:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're being experienced in mind.\NIf we do an incision in the brain, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and delete part of the operating mind,\Nat least the way it operates on the physical plane,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.11,0:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we fail to experience the opposite side of the body.\NThis is common, for instance, after strokes, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where the patient is unable to experience in mind\Neven the existence of a portion of their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.43,0:03:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the body cannot be experienced without the sensation.\NThe sensation can only be experienced in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.30,0:03:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly enough, mind itself cannot experience itself.\NA thought cannot experience its own thoughtness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.30,0:03:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A memory cannot experience its own memoryness.\NA fantasy doesn't experience its own fantasiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That which goes on in mind actually has to be experienced\Nin an energy field which is greater than mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:04:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy field we call consciousness.\NIt is because of consciousness that you are aware
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of what goes on within mind.\NThis is obviously so,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.13,0:04:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the very basic reason for anesthesia.\NWhen with anesthesia we delete consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.42,0:04:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,then there is no awareness of what is going on in mind.\NNo consciousness, no awareness of mind or body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No mind, no awareness of sensations or body.\NConsequently, you will notice by some introspection
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and watching yourself as you go throughout the day\Nthat all of your experience is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.02,0:04:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in a more general way than you had realized\Nin a more general field of experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.02,0:04:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which is almost diffuse.\NIt's almost as though it's everywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.02,0:04:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is within consciousness itself.\NIt's an interesting little experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:05:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out where you think you really experience a thought.\NIf I ask you, where do you think you experience a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.34,0:05:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you will say, in here.\NThat, you see, is the thought about a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that you experience a thought there.\NBut if I ask you now to let go of any belief about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.59,0:05:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,any belief of where you think you are experiencing a thought,\Nand instead ask you to point to exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where a thought is being experienced actually,\Nthe radical truth of where is the phenomena occurring,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.59,0:05:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you will find that it is in no particular place.\NThoughtness is occurring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can say is that thoughtness is occurring,\Nand that you have an awareness of the thoughtness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.69,0:05:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but you are hard put to exactly put your finger on it\Nwhere it could possibly be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:06:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No particular place is where it is being experienced\Nin sort of a general overall way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It is very necessary for us to know this\Nbecause some of the techniques we will be using
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.42,0:06:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,will be ones that cancel a lot of these belief systems\Nthat are at the very basis of human suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.42,0:06:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself, then, is like a movie screen\Nupon which that which is changing is experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you notice, if you look at it,\Nyou will see that all experience is experience of change.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.38,0:06:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the coming and going, the waning and ebbing,\Nthe flux, the movement that you are experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we can experience that which changes\Nis because it is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.51,0:06:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from a background of that which in itself is unchanging.\NIt is because the movie screen is standing still
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can see the movement of the movie.\NSo what is experienced, then, is change,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.54,0:07:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and where it is experienced is consciousness itself,\Nwhich has no exact location.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to be talking about fear\Nas a level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.54,0:07:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to be addressed where it is,\Nnot in its expression and its extension into the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of this, fear of that,\Nnot trying to handle it on the level of the particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.54,0:07:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but handling it as a level of consciousness,\Nbecoming aware of that which we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.54,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which is greater than the fear,\Nlearning to disidentify with the emotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.54,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I am not that,\NI am that in which that is being experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a small thing,\Na phenomenon going on with that greater experience
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which I experience as myself,\Nthat which I really am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are going to be talking about\Nthe letting go of fear and the techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the biggest obstacles to fear,\Nthe difficulty in handling it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fear of fear itself.\NAnd so we will be describing a technique
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.12,0:08:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,which disappears the fear of fear.\NOnce you are no longer afraid of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes a very simple matter.\NWhat is it about fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.28,0:08:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is your fear of it, is it not?\NThe person is afraid of the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.34,0:08:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid of the fear,\Njust as the person going to the dentist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.73,0:08:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is afraid of the pain, you see?\NSo it is that initial fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.89,0:08:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we begin to look at the nature of fear,\Nwe can see that the number of fears are endless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.89,0:08:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of fears are endless,\Nand therefore people become victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.43,0:08:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they become convinced\Nthat the source of fear is outside of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:09:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think the source of fear is outside of yourself,\Nthere is frankly very little you can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.59,0:09:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there is really nothing you can do about it.\NWhat you can do is try and jump at this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.10,0:09:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but because the source is always outside of yourself,\Nyou will always be the victim of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.10,0:09:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,until you begin to realize\Nthat it is the pre-set conditions within you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.10,0:09:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are the source of the fear,\Nwhich you then project onto the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.10,0:09:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course you are sure that you see it out there\Nbecause you just projected it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at fear,\Nwe see how all-pervasive it can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.90,0:09:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you realize that fear is a level of consciousness,\Nthen you realize that from that level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.90,0:09:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fear can be attached to everything.\NTrying to overcome particular fears
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a certain limited value,\Nbut it doesn't change you as a fearful person.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.96,0:09:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't change you as a fearful personality.\NIt doesn't change you as a fearful human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.96,0:10:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of a specific fear may be clinically valuable.\NIt may be practically useful in your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.76,0:10:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't alter who you are.\NToday we are going to be looking more at who you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.76,0:10:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how the conditions of this can be changed,\Nso that you never more feel like a small self
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who is powerless\Nand at the effect of the victimhood of fear itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.76,0:10:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, fear can be like a prefix\Nwhich gets attached to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.98,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are in an energy field,\Nand we are going to be talking today about energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going to be talking about this map of consciousness,\Nwhich we have on the blackboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.17,0:10:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and which we have been using throughout this series.\NThroughout the series we have been talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness here,\Nand you will see fear right about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:11:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to be talking about fear as a level of consciousness.\NThat this level of consciousness here,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.17,0:11:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the lower levels of consciousness,\Nthese are the higher ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.17,0:11:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to be talking about fear.\NWe see that it is a negative emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.17,0:11:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by the direction of the arrow.\NWe see its relative power,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is a mathematical model.\NIn the mathematical model,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we have been able to calibrate the relative energies\Nof these different fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.17,0:11:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, starting from 30, 50, 75.\NAs we go up from the negative emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.17,0:11:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,into the positive emotions,\Nwe see that their actual power,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of physics,\Nactually increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are going to be dealing today with this fear.\NA negative energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates on a relative scale,\Nwhere death would be zero
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.74,0:11:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and enlightenment would be 600,\Nlove would be 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that fear comes out at 100.\NWe are going to be talking about this energy field then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.10,0:12:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to realize that\Nbeing fearful then can attach to anything
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything in your life.\NThere is nothing in your total experience
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.42,0:12:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as a human being\Nto which fear cannot be attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You love your mother,\Nup comes the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what if you lose her?\NYou love your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,up comes the fear of death, sickness.\NYou love money,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.42,0:12:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,up comes the fear of loss,\Nor of being accused of being greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.96,0:12:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you think of,\Nfear can be attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.96,0:12:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You love your automobile,\Nup comes the fear of an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.96,0:12:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A fearful person then attaches the fear to everything.\NSo everything that comes into the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.96,0:12:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming into an energy field of fear,\Nand therefore gets colored with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.96,0:12:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A fear of life itself.\NAnd as the song goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.22,0:12:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid of living and afraid of dying.\NAfraid of living and afraid of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nthis energy field has now contaminated everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.22,0:13:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I am the source of that energy field then,\Nall of my experience comes into the field of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.28,0:13:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything in my life becomes fearful.\NThe future is fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.28,0:13:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Old age, getting older.\NWhat's going to happen to the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.28,0:13:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to my finances?\NWhat's going to happen to my relationships?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to my family?\NWhat's going to happen to my car?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.28,0:13:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to my bank account?\NWhat's going to happen to my country?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to happen to the world?\NAnd so people who get into a global fear
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you about the fears of nuclear annihilation,\Nthe endless fears of intergalactic wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the expansion of the fear\Ndoesn't change the fact that it is still just fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.28,0:13:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamorizing it, making it sound dramatic,\Ndoesn't change that it's just fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.14,0:13:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of intergalactic war and human demolition\Nand the expiration of the human race
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.14,0:13:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is no different than the fear of the child,\Nthe child's fear of the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:14:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,his fear that a dog might bite him.\NWhat's characteristic of all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.14,0:14:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is an energy field called fear.\NFear of what is really immaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.14,0:14:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to have to learn to look away from the thoughts\Nand look instead to the feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.14,0:14:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Look below the feeling to the energy field\Nout of which this feeling is coming
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn how to handle this energy field.\NWhen we do this, we lose our fear of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we lose our fear of fear,\Nwe begin to learn how to handle fear directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Handling fear directly is extremely simple.\NIt is an extremely simple thing to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.98,0:14:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,once we're familiar with some rather simple techniques.\NBecause the world pretty much runs you with fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.98,0:14:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,does it not?\NBecause your life is pretty much run by fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.98,0:14:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've learned a way to not get cornered by fear,\Nyou're beginning to transcend the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're beginning to transcend being victim.\NBecause really, what can the world do in its threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.98,0:15:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How can the world threaten you except through fear?\NTo cut off your bank account,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.98,0:15:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to get audited,\Nto run away from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave you,\Nto fire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.98,0:15:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The gun at your head is always the same gun.\NIt's always the gun of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.98,0:15:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of losing a part of your body.\NThe endless fears, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.30,0:15:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no end to the number of fears.\NThere's no end to the number of fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.30,0:15:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is an end to fearfulness.\NThere is an end to being victim of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.30,0:15:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an end to being afraid of fear.\NWe'll learn today how to lose our fear of fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.29,0:15:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,how to enjoy the process,\Nhow to really start feeling good about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when you realize that you are no longer the small victim,\Nthe worm,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,who is at the effect of this all-pervasive fearfulness.\NSo it's not fear but this energy field of fearfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.29,0:15:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to see that we are in control of it.\NWe are the source of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.29,0:16:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I'm the source of my fearfulness.\NNow we all know, in a different mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing is no longer fearful.\NIt's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a thing that you're afraid of.\NYou say, I am afraid of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you're accompanied by somebody else,\Nwhen you're in a different mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in a humorous mood\Nand having a good time laughing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.22,0:16:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now that thing no longer engenders fear.\NSo the source of fear is not in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.22,0:16:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no way of overcoming one's fear of the world.\NThere is no way the world can be controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.22,0:16:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome your fears.\NAnd society's endless efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.22,0:16:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to end your fears by changing society,\Nby changing the laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.22,0:16:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing the rules,\Nwill not end the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.22,0:16:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because fearfulness is within you.\NOne is the event itself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.22,0:16:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and secondly, how you feel about that.\NSo having more police might make you feel better,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.47,0:17:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but in fact, where are the police going to be\Nwhile your apartment is being robbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At the other end of town, naturally.\NSo therefore, our handling the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is really up to ourself.\NIt comes out of our willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.14,0:17:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to own that we are the source of that fear.\NThat fear is occurring within our own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.14,0:17:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we want to address it\Nwhere it is actually being experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.30,0:17:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people experience fear\Nin a sort of a physical way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.30,0:17:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the first thing we want to do\Nabout a fearful experience
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is to eliminate paying any attention to thoughts.\NThe reason is that a fearful feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,will engender literally millions of thoughts.\NThere is no end to fearful thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.91,0:17:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are coming out of an energy field\Nof fear itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.91,0:17:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which generates an endless series of thoughts.\NClinically speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:18:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,handling the specific thoughts themselves\Nhas a limited value
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and that fearfulness\Nmerely generates more thoughts later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want a technique that will handle fear itself.\NYou might just picture something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.18,0:18:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,fearful in your life,\Nsomething fearful that you expect may happen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or which has happened,\Nor you can just fantasy a fearful experience
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.18,0:18:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,such as being tied to the railroad track\Nand a locomotive is bearing down on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.18,0:18:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at what is being experienced\Nyou'll see when you look past the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.27,0:18:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's being experienced first of all in the body.\NWhat you'll notice is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.27,0:18:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe a tenseness in the stomach muscles,\Na queasy feeling in the stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A shakiness in the arms and the legs\Nor a dryness in the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.27,0:18:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people have cramps,\Nintestinal cramps or intestinal phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:19:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is in your own case\Nyou look within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.34,0:19:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to see what is actually being experienced.\NSee radical truth means
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what's being experienced actually\Nnot what you are thinking about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,not the thoughts about it,\Nthe concepts that you're projecting onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.34,0:19:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're projecting onto the experience.\NNot the labeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.34,0:19:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the putting of a word on it,\Nbut what are you literally experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself.\NThe technique then is to let go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.94,0:19:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing\Nof what is literally being experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.94,0:19:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go resisting the dryness in the mouth.\NLet it be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome it.\NLet go resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the flip-flop feeling in the stomach.\NLet go resisting the trembling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.94,0:19:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in your arms and legs.\NWhen you do this you're focused you see
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.94,0:19:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,away from thoughts\Nonto what is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and you let go,\Nfully let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.94,0:19:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to\Nbeing with those sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:20:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go then is like\Nthe willow tree in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.74,0:20:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming from\Nthe Taoism of China let us say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.96,0:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the ancient wisdom of China\Nwhich states that the oak tree
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.50,0:20:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which resists the wind\Nis susceptible to breaking
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.50,0:20:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willow tree\Nwhich bends with the wind survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.50,0:20:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And so like the willow tree\Nwe bend with the incoming experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.50,0:20:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We let it be.\NWe blend with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.50,0:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome it.\NWe say let's have more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As you do that you'll discover\Nmuch to your surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a limited amount\Nof that sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.50,0:20:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though\Nthe amount of fear that we have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited in quantity.\NHow can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though\Nthis fear is like a pressure tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.02,0:20:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All the suppressed fear\Nthat we've had
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout our lifetime,\Nstarting in our childhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:21:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,all that fear that we couldn't\Nallow ourselves to experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.02,0:21:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't allow ourselves to express,\Nweren't allowed to express,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.02,0:21:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,weren't allowed to have that emotion.\NTo the man let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.21,0:21:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the service,\Nhe wasn't allowed to express
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.21,0:21:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that fearfulness.\NIt was thought to be unmanly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.21,0:21:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe cowardice.\NAnd so that fear gets suppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.21,0:21:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets repressed.\NIt gets pushed down out of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.21,0:21:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Fears have come up by the thousands\Nin our lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.21,0:21:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of which we were even unaware.\NYou see the fear comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.21,0:21:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and unwittingly you brace your back.\NThat fear just got pushed out of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.27,0:21:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you drum your fingers on the desk.\NWhat's happening is the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.27,0:21:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is so quickly suppressed\Nthat you don't even realize
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.27,0:21:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was there.\NAs the years go by,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.94,0:21:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the accumulated energy of this fear,\Nthe energy is what we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.94,0:21:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy behind this fear\Nincreases in pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.94,0:21:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it reaches a certain point,\Nas though you reached a red line
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.94,0:22:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,on the needle of the dial,\Nwhat happens is this pressure now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.94,0:22:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of this fearfulness\Nbegins to express itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.94,0:22:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It spills out, spills over\Ninto our experience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.94,0:22:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to color it.\NIf we don't examine it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.74,0:22:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we think that this fear\Nis coming from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.74,0:22:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We blame the world for it.\NWe think that there is a fearful experience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.74,0:22:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,happening out there.\NLittle do we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.74,0:22:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is merely our own fearfulness\Nbeing projected out into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.74,0:22:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we own that this source of the fear then\Nis our own accumulated fearfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.74,0:22:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we start to welcome\Nand look forward to the opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.74,0:22:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow this fearfulness\Nto run.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.83,0:22:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the sensations\Nand the inner experience of fear itself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.83,0:22:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,remains the same\Nno matter what we think we're afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.83,0:23:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody holds a shotgun\Nto your heart and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.70,0:23:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,give me all your money,\Nwhat are you going to experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.70,0:23:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to experience dry mouth,\Nweakness in the knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.70,0:23:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that old familiar flippy-foppy feeling\Nin the stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.70,0:23:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If an enemy tank rolls up to you,\Nknocks it over,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.89,0:23:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rotate the barrel of the gun\Nand put it right at your forehead,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.89,0:23:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you going to experience?\NYou're going to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.89,0:23:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the same thing.\NThe same thing if somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,holds a mouse over your head.\NYou're going to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.89,0:23:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a dryness in your mouth,\Na queasiness in your stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.89,0:23:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,cramps in the intestine,\Nand that jiggly feeling in your muscles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.89,0:23:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All that you ever have to handle\Nis those sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.89,0:23:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,See, with this fearfulness,\Nsee, with experiencing this technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.89,0:23:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll learn that all you ever have to handle\Nis what you're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.89,0:23:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness itself.\NWhether it's localized within the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.89,0:23:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether more sophisticated\Nafter you've meditated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and worked with this technique,\Nyou'll notice that this experience
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.02,0:24:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening in a general and diffused\Nsort of everywhere-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.02,0:24:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena of the queasy muscles,\Nthe flip-flop in the stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.02,0:24:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the dry mouth,\Nis being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.02,0:24:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in sort of a vague,\Ndiffuse everywhere-ness,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.02,0:24:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just let go resisting that.\NYou just allow the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.02,0:24:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to be there without resisting it.\NBecause you're focused on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.02,0:24:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear begins to diminish.\NFor one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.02,0:24:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're no longer paying attention\Nto the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.02,0:24:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the thoughts themselves\Nare engendering further fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.02,0:24:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're very busy with this technique,\Njust letting go, resisting the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.02,0:24:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're now focused\Non the energy field itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.02,0:24:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind this fearfulness\Nis an energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.02,0:24:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're doing\Nis letting go the resisting
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.02,0:24:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the releasing,\Nprogressive releasing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.02,0:25:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and discharge of this energy.\NBy doing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.69,0:25:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose your fear of fear.\NFear is no longer an awesome terror
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.87,0:25:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that awakens you in the middle of the night.\NIt's nothing but
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.87,0:25:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,an inner emotional experience.\NThe sensations of which
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.87,0:25:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can be easily handled.\NAsk yourself, truly,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.87,0:25:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can you handle a dry mouth?\NOf course you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.87,0:25:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing research and experimenting\Nwith this particular technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.29,0:25:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I had an experience\Nthat I want to share with you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.29,0:25:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because it demonstrates\None of the principles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.29,0:25:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are describing.\NI had had a lifetime fear of heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.29,0:25:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So severe, for instance,\Nthat when I went to visit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.29,0:25:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the Grand Canyon for the first time,\NI literally couldn't get
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.29,0:25:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,within 100 feet of the edge.\NAnd it created that panicky feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.29,0:25:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when I even saw somebody else\Nget near the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.29,0:25:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was using this technique\Nwhenever I could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.96,0:25:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and enjoying the progress\NI was making with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.96,0:25:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just somehow never got around\Nto working on my fear of heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.96,0:26:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was working on fear\Nfrom all its other origins
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.96,0:26:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,within my experience.\NAnd the next time I went back
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.02,0:26:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Grand Canyon\Nwas about a year and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.02,0:26:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or two years later.\NAnd much to my amazement,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.02,0:26:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I could walk up within\Nabout 20 feet of the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.02,0:26:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before this tight feeling\Noccurred in the stomach again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.02,0:26:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I continued to utilize this technique\Nover the next year or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.12,0:26:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, about two years later,\NI went back there
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.12,0:26:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with some members of my family\Nto revisit the canyon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.12,0:26:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And much to my surprise,\NI could walk right up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.12,0:26:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the very edge.\NIn fact, I could dangle
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.12,0:26:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,my feet over the edge.\NI couldn't say I was happy about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.12,0:26:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I did it the impossible.\NI was really so pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.12,0:26:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But what it demonstrated\Nwas the principle
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.12,0:26:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that what I had been releasing\Nwas that accumulated pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.12,0:26:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the accumulated energy\Nof all that fear from a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.12,0:26:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And like a pressure tank,\Nas it released itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.12,0:26:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,now there was less and less\Nto spill over into life's experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.12,0:27:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go then of resisting\Nis so effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.12,0:27:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is it effective?\NBecause we see that resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.12,0:27:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,traps us into a certain\Nstate of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.12,0:27:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And resistance is right\Nin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.12,0:27:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not written on the board,\Nbut when we calibrate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.12,0:27:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a negative energy\Nat about 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.18,0:27:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the important thing\Nover here, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.18,0:27:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is the important thing,\NI'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.18,0:27:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the important thing\Non this line
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.57,0:27:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of this energy field here\Nis that one is trapped by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.57,0:27:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One is trapped by this.\NOne can't get beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.57,0:27:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One becomes victim.\NSo one becomes the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.57,0:27:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of their own fears\Nso long as they own,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.57,0:27:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,don't own that they are\Nthe source of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.57,0:27:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as we rationalize\Nand try to say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.57,0:27:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that the source of the fear\Nis out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.57,0:27:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as we think\Nthe source of the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.57,0:27:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is out there,\Nwe cannot overcome it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.57,0:28:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I begin to own\Nthat I am the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.57,0:28:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the one that sets up\Nthe way in which
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.57,0:28:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I experience things,\Nnow I become the one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.57,0:28:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who is master of the situation.\NMy soul's self-esteem
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.57,0:28:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes affected.\NI am no longer the one
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.57,0:28:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the victim\Nor subject to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.57,0:28:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I am something else\Nother than the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.57,0:28:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, fear is nothing\Nbut an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.57,0:28:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness\Nand I don't give it reality anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by labeling it\Nand by filling in fear of what.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.60,0:28:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The what-ness I'm sure\Nyou see by now is endless.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.60,0:28:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearfulness is attached\Nto everything in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.40,0:28:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by a fearful person.\NChanging the world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.40,0:28:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will not handle it.\NA person can be terribly afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.40,0:28:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very safe situation\Nand afraid not at all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.40,0:29:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very dangerous situation,\None which hypothetically
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.40,0:29:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is dangerous.\NSo we have two situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.50,0:29:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,let us say.\NOne is being mugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.50,0:29:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one thing.\NThen we have the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.62,0:29:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of being mugged.\NThat is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear of being mugged\Nis not the same as being mugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.62,0:29:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is quite possible\Nto have very unfortunate circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.62,0:29:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,happen in one's life\Nand not experience fear at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.62,0:29:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, to experience\Nthat one is the witness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.62,0:29:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the phenomena.\NSuch a thing happened to me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.62,0:29:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in my own life\Nwhen I walked into
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.62,0:29:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a very large-sized rattlesnake\Non the top of a nearby mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NAs I went to step into this cabin,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.62,0:29:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,much to my surprise,\Nhere was a giant rattlesnake
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.29,0:29:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,coiled up there\Nand as I lifted my foot
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.29,0:29:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to step on him,\Nhis head snapped back
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.29,0:29:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and his tongue blew out\Nand he just was ready
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.29,0:29:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and poised to strike.\NSo in that instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.32,0:30:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in that instant,\Nthere was a flash
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.63,0:30:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of fearful thought,\Nthe thought of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.63,0:30:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I could take a club and hit it,\NI could run,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.63,0:30:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I could yell for help,\NI didn't have a gun
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.63,0:30:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but somebody might shoot it.\NYou know, all the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.63,0:30:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic self-protective thoughts\Nthat social consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.76,0:30:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has programmed us with.\NHappily and luckily for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or I probably wouldn't be here\Ngiving you this talk today,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.02,0:30:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had learned this technique.\NInstead, instantly I realized
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.02,0:30:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that my life, frankly,\Ndepended on my utilization
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.02,0:30:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of this technique.\NAnd so what I did instead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.50,0:30:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is I automatically\Nwent into this exact technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.50,0:30:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I automatically let go,\Nwanting to do anything about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.50,0:30:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to handle anything about it,\Nwanting to change anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.50,0:30:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I went into my inner self\Nand I just allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.50,0:30:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner experience\Nto release itself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.50,0:30:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,without any resistance.\NI'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.50,0:31:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I welcomed more of it\Nbecause somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.50,0:31:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when you really get into the\Nexperience of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.50,0:31:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,inner consciousness,\Nyou really see that your survival
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.50,0:31:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,really depends on this\Nand it has all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.56,0:31:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I saw that my\Nsurvival really depended
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.56,0:31:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on the excellence\Nwith which I let go
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.56,0:31:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrendered and released\Nand let go resisting the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.56,0:31:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As I did,\Nthe fearful thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.59,0:31:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly disappeared\Nand I felt like a profound
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.66,0:31:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,state of peace\Nsettle on the snake and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.66,0:31:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like I became the witness,\Nnot the witness confined
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.07,0:31:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to this body,\Nbut the witness in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.07,0:31:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which seemed to have no dimension.\NAnd this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.17,0:31:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,formless dimension\Nwas then the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.17,0:31:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence\Nof a state of peacefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.17,0:31:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This profound state of peacefulness\Nwas of such power
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.17,0:31:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that it prevailed\Nover the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.17,0:32:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of both the snake\Nand the personality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.17,0:32:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of this person speaking to you.\NAnd so,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.17,0:32:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the snake looked at me\Ninterestedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.17,0:32:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,having not seen a human being,\NI don't think in his whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.17,0:32:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,much less a foot away.\NAnd I looked at the rattlesnake
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.46,0:32:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with great curiosity\Nand thought of him as brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.46,0:32:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of us were included\Nin the oneness of this space
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.46,0:32:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own beingness together\Nin a state of extreme intimacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.46,0:32:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of it came\Nsort of an inner joyfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.46,0:32:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I like felt\Nthe love for the snake arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.46,0:32:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises out of the field,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.46,0:32:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,once the fear is removed.\NIf we look at our
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.80,0:32:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,scale of consciousness over here\Nthat we've been talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.80,0:32:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we can track what had happened.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.80,0:32:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we track what had happened.\NThe fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.80,0:32:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which has a negative energy field,\Nwhich the snake
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.80,0:32:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would have instantly picked up.\NHe instantly would have picked up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.80,0:32:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or instantly would have picked up anger.\NMy desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.80,0:32:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say,\Nto strike at him
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.80,0:33:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and his responses\Nthrough his energy system
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.80,0:33:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are so fast,\Nthe strike would have happened
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.80,0:33:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,before I could have moved\Nmy shin out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.80,0:33:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\Nbecause of the severe threat
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.80,0:33:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the circumstance\Nand the circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.80,0:33:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you,\NI let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.80,0:33:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Ndid I ever let go?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.80,0:33:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I jumped right through\Nthe willingness to let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.80,0:33:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right through the acceptance,\Nright to the love,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.80,0:33:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right to the joy,\Nright to a state
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.80,0:33:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of profound peace.\NI would say
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.80,0:33:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,if I calibrated\Nthe energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.80,0:33:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of that experience,\Nit would probably come out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.80,0:33:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,around 599,\Nmaybe 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.80,0:33:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there was\Nthe feeling of a presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.80,0:33:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite presence\Nwhose essential nature
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.80,0:33:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of peace\Nand whose power
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.80,0:33:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite\Nand that controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.80,0:33:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole experience.\NAnd thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.80,0:33:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,both the snake\Nand myself
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.80,0:33:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,transcended fear.\NThe falsity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.80,0:33:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of another one\Nof the mind's belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.80,0:33:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have to learn\Nto let go of.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.80,0:33:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea\Nthat fear
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.02,0:34:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source\Nof our safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.02,0:34:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice\Nthat the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.04,0:34:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of worships fear\Nas though it's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.04,0:34:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of a demi-god.\NAnd the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.04,0:34:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,has sort of a program\Nthat says,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.04,0:34:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason\NI'm alive
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.14,0:34:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to\Nmy fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.14,0:34:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because\NI allow fears
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.46,0:34:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to decide\Nwhat I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.19,0:34:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to do\Nthat I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.19,0:34:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A little introspection\Nwill show you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.26,0:34:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that this belief system\Nis going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.26,0:34:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.15,0:34:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if I wasn't afraid\Nof being poor
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.15,0:34:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in my old age,\NI wouldn't get insurance,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.15,0:34:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\NIf I wasn't afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.15,0:34:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of an automobile accident,\NI wouldn't drive safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.15,0:34:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,\Nthe person begins
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.82,0:34:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to ascribe\Nthe source
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.82,0:34:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of their aliveness,\Nthe source
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.82,0:34:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of their life,\Nthe god of their life,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.82,0:34:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is fear.\NThey really begin
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.82,0:34:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to worship fear.\NNow we see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.08,0:34:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,from the example\Nthat I just described
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.08,0:34:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that the opposite\Nis true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.14,0:34:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What ensures\Nour survival
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.14,0:35:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is the absence\Nof fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.21,0:35:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you might say\Nthat we have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.21,0:35:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,managed to survive\Nin spite
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.21,0:35:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of our fears\Nbut not because
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.21,0:35:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of them.\NAs you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.04,0:35:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make decisions\Nbased on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.04,0:35:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,rational choice,\Nbased on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.04,0:35:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,our knowingness,\Non our knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.04,0:35:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,based on our value,\Ncoming from
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.04,0:35:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the beingness\Nof that which
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.04,0:35:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we really are\Nwithout fear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.04,0:35:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,entering the picture\Nat all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.00,0:35:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All day long\Nwe make decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.00,0:35:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that are just\Nbased on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.00,0:35:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our awareness\Nof reality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.00,0:35:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with no fear\Nparticularly
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.00,0:35:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,involved.\NFear is not
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.35,0:35:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary.\NThe idea
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.35,0:35:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that fear\Nis good
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.35,0:35:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for you,\Nthat it's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.35,0:35:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,valuable,\Nthat it has
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.35,0:35:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds\Nof mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.35,0:35:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,values,\Npeople will
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.35,0:35:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,look back\Nand rationalize
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.35,0:35:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how fear\Ngot them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.35,0:35:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to do this\Nand fear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.35,0:35:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,got them\Nto do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.35,0:35:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\NI can say
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.35,0:36:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's too bad.\NToo bad they didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.35,0:36:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,do it out of\Nlove for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,out of love\Nfor their fellow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.35,0:36:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,human beings.\NToo bad they didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.35,0:36:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,do it out of\Nlove for life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.58,0:36:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,itself,\Nlove for their
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.58,0:36:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,own aliveness,\Nlove for their
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.58,0:36:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,body.\NWhy not do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.58,0:36:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,this?\NWhy not keep
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.58,0:36:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it healthy and\Nhappy because
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.58,0:36:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you love it\Nand value it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.58,0:36:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not because\Nyou're afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.58,0:36:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of a heart\Nattack or
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.58,0:36:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid of\Nsomething.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.56,0:36:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it out of\Nvaluing it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.56,0:36:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.56,0:36:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ways to let\Ngo more
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.56,0:36:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of this fear\Nwill describe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.14,0:36:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,another technique\Nwhich I call
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.14,0:36:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the worst\Nscenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.14,0:36:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nif you follow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.14,0:36:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,fear as you\Nwill see,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.14,0:36:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if you ask\Nyourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.14,0:36:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are you afraid\Nof driving
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.14,0:36:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your car?\NWell, I might
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.14,0:36:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,have an accident.\NWell, why are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.14,0:36:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you afraid of\Nan accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.14,0:36:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because\Nthen I might
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.14,0:36:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,get injured.\NWell, what if
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.14,0:37:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you got injured?\NWell, then I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.14,0:37:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,might suffer\Npain, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.26,0:37:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll find\Nthat every fear
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.64,0:37:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimately will\Nlead you to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.64,0:37:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of\Ndeath.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.64,0:37:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of the\Nbody's dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.64,0:37:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll lead you\Nto fears of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.64,0:37:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,whether other\Npeople like
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.64,0:37:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NWhat fear does
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.64,0:37:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that bring up\Nand what fear
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.64,0:37:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is the basis\Nof that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.64,0:37:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally get\Nto the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.64,0:37:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario.\NThe worst
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.64,0:37:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario,\Nlet's say your
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.64,0:37:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,financial fears,\Nare that you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.64,0:37:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will totally\Nrun out of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.64,0:37:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,money,\Nhave no
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.64,0:37:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,place to\Nlive,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.64,0:37:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,no money\Nfor food,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.64,0:37:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,no money\Nfor clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.64,0:37:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so you will\Nend up
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.64,0:37:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,semi-naked\Nsomewhere on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.09,0:37:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a street\Nand constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.09,0:37:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,let go,\Nresisting the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.09,0:37:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling of this\Nand picture the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.09,0:37:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,worst scenario.\NWhat's the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.09,0:37:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,possible thing\Nthat could happen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.09,0:37:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to you?\NYou end up
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.11,0:38:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the poor farm.\NYou end up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.11,0:38:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting on the\Nstreet corner
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.11,0:38:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as a bag lady\Nor a bag man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.75,0:38:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So you allow\Nyourself to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.75,0:38:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,picture the worst\Nscenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.75,0:38:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are\Nwith your bag
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.75,0:38:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,next to you\Nsitting on the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.75,0:38:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,cold street\Ncorner at
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.04,0:38:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,midnight\Nfriendless.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.00,0:38:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you continue\Nthe same
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.00,0:38:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,practice.\NYou go within
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.00,0:38:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself and\Nyou keep
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.03,0:38:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go,\Nresisting the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.03,0:38:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,inner experience\Nof what is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.03,0:38:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up\Nnow.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.03,0:38:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you do\Nthat,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.03,0:38:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty soon\Nthe fear
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.03,0:38:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,will run\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.03,0:38:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear\Nof the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.06,0:38:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario\Nwill run
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.06,0:38:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,out.\NEventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.06,0:38:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if you continue\Nthis practice
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.06,0:38:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,long enough,\Nyou'll finally
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.10,0:38:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,sit down\Nwith the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.10,0:38:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,worst\Nscenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.86,0:38:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is\Nthe worst
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.86,0:38:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.86,0:38:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That most of\Nus can visualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.86,0:38:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of us\Nwho still think
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.86,0:39:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are\Nthat material
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.02,0:39:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,body,\Nthat that's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.02,0:39:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,all there is\Nto us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.02,0:39:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nsooner or later
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.02,0:39:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we come to\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.02,0:39:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we\Ncome to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.02,0:39:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what we do\Nis we sit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.02,0:39:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with it,\Nthe same
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.12,0:39:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as we sat\Nwith any
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.12,0:39:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of our\Npast
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.12,0:39:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,beliefs.\NYou have no
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.12,0:39:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,experience\Nof the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.12,0:39:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,truth\Nof that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.82,0:39:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nyou have to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.82,0:39:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,label it\Nfantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.82,0:39:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a\Nfantasy in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.05,0:39:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind.\NWhat you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.05,0:39:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,actually\Nexperience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.05,0:39:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is you\Npicture
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.85,0:39:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that and\Nlet go
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.85,0:39:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,resisting\Nthose feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.85,0:39:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and sensations.\NA very
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.85,0:39:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,surprising\Nthing is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.85,0:39:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in store\Nfor you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.42,0:39:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is the\Nfact that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.19,0:39:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're\Nnot
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.19,0:39:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,going to\Nbe
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.19,0:39:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nperson
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.19,0:40:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you\Nwant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.19,0:40:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to be.\NAnd I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.19,0:40:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,want to\Nbe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.19,0:40:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nperson
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.93,0:40:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.93,0:40:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,want\Nto be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.93,0:40:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I\Nwant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.93,0:40:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to be\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.93,0:40:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,person\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.93,0:40:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you\Nwant
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.92,0:40:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to be.\NBecause I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.92,0:40:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from\Nchoice
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.92,0:40:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.92,0:40:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is\Nno fear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.92,0:40:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in that,\Nthe fear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.92,0:40:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears.\NThe worst
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.92,0:40:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that\Ncan happen
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.92,0:40:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is I end\Nup on a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.92,0:40:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,street corner\Nand live
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.40,0:40:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind\Nof life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.40,0:40:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the\Nfear about
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.40,0:40:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it is\Ngone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.40,0:40:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I may\Nnot choose
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.40,0:40:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind\Nof a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.40,0:40:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,life,\Nif I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.40,0:40:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,should run\Nout of money
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.40,0:40:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,someday.\NNo matter
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.66,0:40:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how many\Nmillions you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.66,0:40:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,have,\Nthat fear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.66,0:41:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is there.\NThe thought
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.66,0:41:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that I\Ncan earn
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.66,0:41:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,more and\Nmore money
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.66,0:41:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and pile\Nup more
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.66,0:41:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and more\Nin the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.66,0:41:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,bank,\Netc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.69,0:41:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is futile.\NI know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody\Nwho was
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.69,0:41:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,recently\Nworth
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.36,0:41:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,$60\Nmillion
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.36,0:41:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and today\Nis putting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.36,0:41:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,six locks\Non our
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.36,0:41:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,doors,\Nhiring more
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.36,0:41:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,police.\NIt's owning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.36,0:41:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm\Nthe source
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.36,0:41:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of my\Nown experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.13,0:41:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm\Nmaster of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.13,0:41:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it,\Nthat I can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.22,0:41:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,handle\Nit,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.22,0:41:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm\Ngreater
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.22,0:41:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,than that.\NThe mind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.70,0:41:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will,\Nof course,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.70,0:41:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will always\Ntry to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.70,0:41:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,justify\Nour
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.70,0:41:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fears.\NThe mind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.96,0:41:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will try to\Njustify
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.28,0:41:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our fears.\NBut it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.28,0:41:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will try\Nto justify
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.28,0:41:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our fears.\NI think
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.28,0:42:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's\Nthe most
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,important\Nthing to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.50,0:42:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,think\Nabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.50,0:42:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm\Nnot
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.50,0:42:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,going\Nto
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.50,0:42:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,go\Nout
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.50,0:42:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nchoice
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.50,0:42:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in a\Nway that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.50,0:42:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nis not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.50,0:42:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,going\Nto bring
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.50,0:42:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,on such\NAnd my free choice is made by a mind which is not fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.54,0:42:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the not-fearfulness is why I'm alive today to talk to you.\NIt was not being afraid that held back the rattlesnake from striking when he was really
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.90,0:42:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,only inches away.\NIt's the loss of the fear, the letting go of the fearfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.19,0:42:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And having been in very severe, you might say to the eyes of the usual observer, dangerous\Nsituations, and experienced only joy and happiness and trust in those circumstances, and walked
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.57,0:43:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,through cutthroats who would have really attacked a person who was holding fear and did it with\Na happy, gleeful smile on the faces of everyone, I mean, they got off on it that a guy like
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.75,0:43:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,me would walk right through them, you know, with their guns and chains and knives.\NHad I come from fear, they would have challenged that and danger would really have arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.64,0:43:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the letting go.\NLetting go of the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.40,0:43:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they saw there was no fear, there was nothing to bounce off.\NLetting go of the worst scenario then is extremely beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.84,0:43:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As we do this, we'll get to an awareness that something has been setting up the fear within\Nus, that now we've lost our fear of fear, and when it arises, we just walk around with
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.64,0:43:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NI've walked around with fear for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.20,0:43:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I let fear run one time for two solid weeks.\NThat trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.02,0:43:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That electric feeling ran through the body.\NI went about my business, just kept letting it run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.10,0:43:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I just let it run.\NSo let it run.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.46,0:44:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You let it run when you realize it'll run out.\NBut as we do that, you may come across that there is another source underlying this fear
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.20,0:44:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with, and we come up against guilt as the source of fear.\NWe now begin to see the value of work that the world calls spiritual consciousness, whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.86,0:44:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,terminology.\NWe begin to see the value of, for instance, techniques such as concentrating on the value
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.00,0:44:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of forgiving.\NWe see forgiving our self and forgiving our human beings, and turning over any judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.60,0:44:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to God.\NWe begin to see, if not to God, to some higher power, some energy, fate, whatever you want
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.60,0:44:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to call it.\NWe find that by letting go, condemning our self and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.18,0:44:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that by letting go, condemning our self and others.\NThat the unconscious guilt, that that builds up, then also begins to alleviate fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.48,0:45:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because fear, then, you see, is held in mind because we expect the return of our attacks.\NWe expect revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.54,0:45:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect retaliation.\NSo every negative thought that we hold, every hostile thought that we hold about others,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.25,0:45:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,engenders our own fearfulness, because on the psychic plane, on the mental plane, on\Nthe plane which is invisible to the naked eye. It is though we are building up for ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.59,0:45:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is going to come back to ourself. And so we learn that fearfulness begins to\Ndiminish as we let go our angriness, hostile, critical, our thoughts which condemn others
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.48,0:45:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that make them wrong. And we learn the value of letting go the thoughts that make other\Npeople wrong. We begin to value them and love them for their beingness, for what they
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.40,0:46:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are. We begin to see ourself as different. Therefore we begin to see others as different.\NWe become willing to forgive, willing to forget, willing to overlook. We begin to see that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.96,0:46:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that we have condemned in others are really expressions of their humanness.\NWhat we have been condemning in ourself and what we have been condemning in everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.14,0:46:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,else is their humanness.\NThe innocence of the little child within them that believed everything it heard as
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.42,0:46:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it grew up. What do you suppose the political persuasion of a person is as they grew up\Nas an innocent child? The consciousness of the child is innocent, is it not? It loves
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.86,0:46:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,its parents, it trusts its parents, it loves the mother. And therefore the innocence of\Nthe child is what gets programmed. It is the innocent child that believes everything that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.82,0:46:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it is told, that the teacher tells it.\NThe political programming that comes in via television, via the political system of the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.60,0:47:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,country. I ask you, who bought that? Who bought what you believe? To the listener right\Nnow, all the belief systems in your mind, who bought them? You know who bought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.71,0:47:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind of the innocent child within you. Because that innocent child's mind, the nature\Nof consciousness itself, has not changed since you were born. That which is listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.04,0:47:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,me right now.\NIs the innocent consciousness of the child. Listening, alertly, saying, should I believe
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.36,0:47:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what he's saying? Should I take it within myself? The innocent child never dies. That\Ninnocence is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.33,0:47:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you begin to see that intrinsic innocence and you realize that all the things that you\Never learned that ended up wrong were bought out of that intrinsic not knowing the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.03,0:47:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and learning that which was not the truth. Therefore we're willing to let go of our condemnation\Nof others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.75,0:48:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're beginning to own our own innocence and the innocence of others. Misfortunate, perhaps.\NRegretful that the misinformation came into the innocent mind. You might look at the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.88,0:48:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of as the hardware of the computer and its belief systems as the software. Can the\Nfive year old child in Russia think other than the political system that he hears in
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.52,0:48:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,his kindergarten from his fellow students, from those parents, from his friends, from\Nhis parents, from his family, from his grandparents, you begin to see it's out of his not knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.20,0:48:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's out of the innocence of his not knowingness, that he believes what he believes.\NWe're willing to forgive others then and instead of condemning them, understand them. And out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.32,0:48:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of this understanding then, develops a certain compassion. The compassionate person has no\Nfears. What is there to fear in a compassionate world? Inasmuch as we're the source of our
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.50,0:48:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,own experience.\NOur compassion as we own it back within ourself, as we see our own innocence and the innocence of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.20,0:49:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,others, brings to us the experience of a compassionate and loving world. No longer do\Nwe walk around fearfully because we are not creating it ourselves anymore. We see that we
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.41,0:49:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,were the source of our fears. The world was never the source of our fear. We are the source of the\Nfear. Having let go creating it, having let go propagating it through the endless guilt which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.49,0:49:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about and through the endless judgments which social conditioning has brought us into\Nthe habit of, having let go of this now the unconscious guilt diminishes. The letting go of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.18,0:49:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious guilt progresses outside of our awareness. When we decide instead of condemning\Nthat person, I'm going to try to understand him. Every time we do that, our own store of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.31,0:49:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,unconscious guilt goes down. As our store of unconscious guilt goes down, the\Nexistence of our own conscience goes down. The existence of our own conscience goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.01,0:49:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The existence of our own conscience goes down. The existence of our own conscience goes down.\Nexpectation of retaliation goes down. You see, in the unconscious, it's an eye for an
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.75,0:50:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,eye, a tooth for a tooth. If you wish somebody would drop dead, what do you suppose its equal\Nis in your unconscious mind? That you should drop dead. You don't think that your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.88,0:50:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,about if only your so-and-so would drop dead has anything to do with your fears of a heart\Nattack? Of course they do. As you let go wishing other people would drop dead, you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.95,0:50:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,curiously enough that your fear and obsession that you're going to get a coronary, you might\Nget a coronary, and all the dietary nonsense that goes with that will diminish. Instead you're very
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.37,0:50:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,peaceful about the whole thing. When you go, you go. If you stay, you stay. Big deal. What you value\Nis life and you no longer focus on the potential ending of that life. So you come into a different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.09,0:50:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,experience of the experiencing of life. You come into a different feeling about who you are.\NSee, I am that in which this experiencing is going on. And like the ox herding pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.86,0:51:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've referred to before, instead of being dragged about by the ox of fear against\Nour will with bleeding knees and rumpled clothes, now we tie this ox to a tree. Now we've located
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.32,0:51:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the culprit, where he is, you see. Having let go our fear of him now, we've become the\Nmaster. We get on top of the ox, the ox becomes tame. We are
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.76,0:51:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the master.\NMaster, we've identified now with that which we really are, no longer the victim, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.03,0:51:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Victim comes out of unconsciousness. It means being unaware of this game setup that's been\Ngoing on within our mind. Merely becoming aware of it means that you're already out
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.69,0:51:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. By the time you've heard this talk today, you've gotten up from being victim.\NYou're already tying this ox to the tree. That's what we're doing today, is tying that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.78,0:52:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ox to the tree. And then, as you practice these techniques we've described, you'll be\Nsitting on top of the ox. When the fear comes along, you welcome it. You say, great, what
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.11,0:52:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,an opportunity to let go more of that. Because by now you're feeling the benefit. You're\Nfeeling the decrease of fear and fears that you've had your whole lifetime. Little do
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.85,0:52:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,people realize the extent of the fear that they're holding until it begins to disappear.\NAnd then it's mind-boggling. You say, I never realized that was such a fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.27,0:52:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fearful human being.\NPerhaps more easily understood by referring back to this map of consciousness, so that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.24,0:52:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see how the energy fields here relate to the way we experience the world. You see,\Nmind is so powerful that the way it holds your experience literally determines your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.24,0:52:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. Fearfulness creates a certain view of the world, and it becomes a self-fulfillment.\NSelf-fulfilling prophecy. In psychoanalysis, psychiatry, it's called the self-fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.09,0:53:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,prophecy. And recent university research, as well as our own research in Sedona, shows\Nthat what you hold in mind tends to make it happen within what you think is the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.71,0:53:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of your own experience, then, becomes the external representation, actually, of\Nwhat you have been holding in mind. So that your life, the world, is really a world of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.15,0:53:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,mirrors.\NWhat you're actually seeing, what you're actually experiencing, is a projection of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.06,0:53:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,your own level of consciousness. This is hard to believe and hard to really fully grasp,\Nbut to give us a glimpse at it, it's a whole field of study in itself. On this map of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.18,0:53:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,let's compare the level of consciousness with its emotion and our view of the world, and\Nhow this would give us a view of God if we believed in such consciousness.
