Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.68,0:58:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God, if there is a God at all. There's me and there's God, but the two of us have no\Nrelationship. The frustration of this frustrating world of desire leads to anger, resentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.86,0:59:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred, grievance, war, murder. The expansion, the over-expansion of the angry person, the\Nstanding out of the blood vessels, the angry animal flares up with anger. The angry person
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.44,0:59:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,sees this as a competitive world. When somebody opens up another used car lot next to him,\Nhe's angry. He thinks that this person is going to take his business away. See, he hasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.37,0:59:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,moved up to a world of cooperation, which knows that the more used car lots near you,\Nthe greater the business, because it draws people from everywhere. So he wouldn't think
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.21,0:59:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of cooperating. Instead, he thinks of competition. So he's polarized. It's me against\Nthem, you see. And therefore, he sees a competitive world and a retaliatory God, who out of angriness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.23,0:59:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is very punishing. This is the angry God that will punish you, retaliate against you, and\Nseek revenge. I am a jealous, vengeful God who will get you. I'm out to get you. So God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.17,1:00:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is somebody who is your enemy. He's out to get you, you see, out to get you. How can\Nyou relax and reach any kind of awareness in that kind of an angry energy field? You
