Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.87,1:00:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,one of being inflated. This person lives in a world of status. When he walks down the\Nsame city street, what he sees is not only your Cadillac, but the year and the model.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.29,1:00:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even realize they came in models. I thought a Caddy was a Caddy. No, sir. There\Nare different models of Cadillacs, I've discovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.87,1:00:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And so whether you have a, I forget the name of them, but whatever they are, one has more\Nstatus than the other. So the interest in other human beings then is their position.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.50,1:00:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's president of so-and-so, or he's only a blue collar worker, or it isn't the money,\Nit's the status that the money gives them. What comes out of pridefulness? What kind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.06,1:01:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of a God can you see out of pridefulness? Well, you've probably got two options. Because\Nof denial and because of intellectual arrogance, you can say that my left brain intellect denies
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.97,1:01:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a God, and that's atheism. Or you can say my position is the right one, and\Neverybody else is therefore wrong, and you end up with bigotry. This is the source of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.80,1:01:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,all the religious wars. My view of religion is right, therefore, yours must be wrong.\NSo pridefulness leads us into a polarized position of me right, you wrong. This is the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.94,1:01:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,world of win-lose. The anxiety that goes with win-lose, so the person in pride is defensive.\NThis is the world of win-lose. As we move up to courage then, we see what happens is
