Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.90,1:02:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,able to face, to cope, to handle. They become empowered because they have begun to tell\Nthe truth about themself. The person from the level of courage walks down the same street,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.98,1:02:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and what does he see? He sees the power of God. He sees the power of God. He sees the\Npower of the light. He sees the ability to move. He sees the power of God. He sees that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.56,1:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he has power. He sees the power of God by just looking at everything he's able to see.\NHe sees a challenging exciting world of opportunity. What a thrilling world of growing, of learning,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.80,1:02:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of expanding, of watching others grow. The inner joy that comes from expanding your own\Nspace. Courage is what settled the United States of America. It settled the West. It
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.82,1:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,creates all the industrial empires. It creates all our scientific enterprises. It's what\Ngot us to the Moon. The world of exciting opportunity of growth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.96,1:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,expansion. What kind of a God is the God of that level of consciousness? The person of that level\Nof consciousness, for the first time, has an open mind. He doesn't come from, I got the answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.82,1:03:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't come from vengeful negativity. He says, for the first time, I wonder if there is such a\Nbeing. I wonder if there is something greater than the personal self. I'm open to learn about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.86,1:03:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. He then treats the God question the same as he does the world question. An exciting world of\Nexploration. And let me tell you, spiritual research is extremely exciting. The things
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.74,1:03:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that you discover. As we move up to the next energy field, then, courage has resulted in being\Nunattached. Hmm. This person says, it's okay if I get the job. It's okay if I don't. He's released.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.82,1:03:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not run by the world. His power greatly increases because now,\Nwell, he's no longer victim. Hmm. You can't control him now anymore. He says, if I get the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.39,1:03:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,job, great. If I don't, I'll just find another job. If this person stays in my life, great. If\Nthey don't, I'll find somebody else to be with. They're no longer living in fear. They've moved
