Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.65,1:04:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with things, you see. This person waits on your table. It's okay if he waits on you. It's\Nokay if he doesn't. This person begins to experience a willingness to be of service,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.85,1:04:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain happiness. And this person views the world as friendly. When you're willing,\Nthe world is friendly. Now you walk down the street, you see all the friendly people,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.89,1:05:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,potentially friendly. All you have to do is walk up to an old lady and say, hi, what a beautiful\Nday. She goes, hey, nobody's talked to me all morning. Isn't that nice? The world is a friendly
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.65,1:05:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,place, and God becomes perhaps a promising and a hopeful concept. The god of a friendly world\Nwould become a friendly god. Even if you don't believe in them, you begin to trust them. If you
