Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.85,1:05:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. He's gonna understand human nature. He's not gonna throw me into the pitfires of hell for\Nhuman. He created me as human. I am his handiwork. What is he going to do, condemn his own self?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.96,1:05:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So there for God, certain trust in God if there is such a thing. As we move up to acceptance,\Nwhat's happening in acceptance is you've begun to own yourself as the source of your own
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.19,1:06:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,power. You are the creator of the happiness in your own life now. And that transformation\Nin consciousness brings a feeling of adequacy and confidence and life, the view of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.85,1:06:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,now is harmonious. As you walk down the street, you see the subtle, beautiful naturalness\Nof how everything interacts, that everything is really where it should be, that everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.77,1:06:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is wanting to be what they are. The bag lady is there because she wants to be a bag lady.\NNobody's forced her to be that. She's chosen to be that which she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.65,1:06:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We can stop blaming God for everything. We can stop blaming God for everything. We can\Nstop blaming the wonderful, beautiful, perfect, awesome all that God did. We can stop blaming
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.79,1:06:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves for all the things that understanding has done to our soul. We can stop blaming\NGod for everything. We can block not surprised at matters of personal themselves whether
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.31,1:06:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nor his Mate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.30,1:07:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,very powerful level, because this is unconditional love in which we begin to nurture, support\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.98,1:07:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We are willing to forgive it.\NBeginning revelation occurs because of the release of these endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.08,1:07:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see the lovingness that is everywhere.\NWe see the lovingness in nature, the lovingness of the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.90,1:07:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the natural lovingness of the child within everybody.\NThe loving heart of the child is still alive in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.58,1:07:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't experience it, it's because you don't know how to tune into it.\NBut I tell you, the innocent loving heart of the child is in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.32,1:07:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be appealed to.\NThat's why the merciless killer, in the presence of a loving person, becomes harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.84,1:07:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of the fearful person who creates the space for him to attack, he attacks.\NThis loving person then experiences a safe world, and God must, of necessity, be of at
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.33,1:07:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,least as high a level of consciousness as you are.\NAnd therefore unconditionally loving.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.45,1:08:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the truth of this brings you into a joyfulness.\NJoyfulness brings about a transfiguration in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.35,1:08:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings you into compassion.\NThe inner serenity of the compassionate person begins to see the perfection of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.67,1:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfection of creation.\NThis unconditional love of the Creator creates a oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.27,1:08:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to experience a oneness.\NThe oneness of all beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.79,1:08:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore all of life, in all its expressions, are sacred, beginning awareness of the sacredness\Nof life and merging into an illuminated enlightened state, into a blissfulness, into a feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.66,1:08:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite peace, in which the total oneness of creation brings an awareness of God as\Nthe essence of beingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.18,1:08:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As I stood on top of this mountain in the presence of the rest of the world, I saw the\Nrattlesnake.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.36,1:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that transfixed both of us?\NInto a state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.48,1:09:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Into a state of oneness.\NI couldn't really say in that state that the aliveness, the life of the snake and the life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.29,1:09:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of myself were two different lives.\NIt's as though there was one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.91,1:09:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The two were being controlled by the nature of the one, that which brought what seemed\Nto be the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.46,1:09:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Together as one experience.\NThere was really only one experience going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.96,1:09:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The one experience was being experienced, you might say, through the two.\NThe two experiencing their oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.22,1:09:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No thought of attack therefore arose, because the energy field of that experience had already\Nrisen up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.58,1:09:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The feeling of infinite peace.\NIt's called by many, peace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.42,1:10:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called by psychology.\NIt's called by psychologists, perhaps, peak experience, Maslow's term for peak experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.76,1:10:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning one has transcended all these levels, you see, and experienced the truth of their\Nbeingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.50,1:10:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain teachings that say there are only two emotions at all.\NThere is love and there is fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.22,1:10:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that all these negative feelings from love on down are nothing but variations of\Nfear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.78,1:10:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it certainly can be looked at that way.\NYou can see all of these as expressions of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.95,1:10:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of moral wrong.\NFear of the inability to survive and exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.35,1:10:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear over the loss of the source of one's happiness.\NFear that one won't get.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.05,1:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger over the intrinsic fear that not getting brings to the person.\NSo we could say that they are all forms of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.91,1:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There really are two expressions only.\NThat which is love.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.19,1:11:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Starts here and becomes infinite in its expression.\NAnd that which is fearful and begins here and goes ever downward in its expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.83,1:11:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the handling of all the negative feelings arises out of the willingness, the\Nwillingness to accept that we have the power within us to handle this inner fearfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.66,1:11:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and to recognize that we are the source of it, to stop projecting it onto the world or\Nonto God.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.38,1:11:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No one created a fearful world.\NThere is no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.29,1:11:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The fearful world is within us.\NWe carry it with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.13,1:11:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus we can let it go.\NWe can let the fear of the fear go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.45,1:11:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can let the fear itself go and move into the presence of love itself.
